cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.AR 

This paper is about implementing binarized convolutional neural networks on GPU-based platforms for efficient inference on resource-constrained devices. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the computational load and memory footprint, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses bit-wise operations, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
